The comment claims `FixedTimeEquals` returns false “without short-circuiting” when byte arrays differ in length. In .NET, `FixedTimeEquals` only guarantees constant-time comparison when the spans have the same length; differing lengths can be rejected immediately. To avoid misleading future changes, please reword this to not rely on constant-time behavior across length mismatches (or explicitly normalize/compare lengths first if that property is required).
```suggestion
            // SECURITY: use CryptographicOperations.FixedTimeEquals so equal-
            // length password comparisons do not leak information through
            // per-byte timing differences. Do not rely on fixed-time behavior
            // when the byte arrays differ in length; that case may be rejected
            // immediately by the BCL implementation.
```

`generateToken` produces a deterministic, non-expiring bearer token derived only from `GENPRES_PASSWORD` and a constant string. If this token is ever leaked (e.g., via logs, browser memory inspection, etc.), it grants indefinite access to admin endpoints until the password is rotated. Consider issuing a time-bound token (include an expiry and HMAC/sign it) or generating a random per-session token stored server-side and validated on each request.
```suggestion
    let private tokenLifetime = System.TimeSpan.FromHours(1.0)


    let private generateToken () =
        match Env.getItem "GENPRES_PASSWORD" with
        | None -> ""
        | Some secret ->
            let expiresAt =
                System.DateTimeOffset.UtcNow.Add(tokenLifetime).ToUnixTimeSeconds()

            let nonceBytes = Array.zeroCreate<byte> 32
            System.Security.Cryptography.RandomNumberGenerator.Fill nonceBytes

            let nonce = System.Convert.ToBase64String(nonceBytes)
            let payload = $"{expiresAt}:%s{nonce}"
            let payloadBytes = System.Text.Encoding.UTF8.GetBytes(payload)

            use hmac =
                new System.Security.Cryptography.HMACSHA256(System.Text.Encoding.UTF8.GetBytes(secret))

            let signatureBytes = hmac.ComputeHash(payloadBytes)
            let encodedPayload = System.Convert.ToBase64String(payloadBytes)
            let encodedSignature = System.Convert.ToBase64String(signatureBytes)

            $"{encodedPayload}.%s{encodedSignature}"


    let private validateToken (token: string) =
        if System.String.IsNullOrWhiteSpace(token) then
            false
        else
            match Env.getItem "GENPRES_PASSWORD" with
            | None -> false
            | Some secret ->
                let parts = token.Split('.')

                if parts.Length <> 2 then
                    false
                else
                    try
                        let payloadBytes = System.Convert.FromBase64String(parts[0])
                        let providedSignatureBytes = System.Convert.FromBase64String(parts[1])

                        use hmac =
                            new System.Security.Cryptography.HMACSHA256(
                                System.Text.Encoding.UTF8.GetBytes(secret)
                            )

                        let expectedSignatureBytes = hmac.ComputeHash(payloadBytes)

                        if
                            providedSignatureBytes.Length <> expectedSignatureBytes.Length
                            || not (
                                System.Security.Cryptography.CryptographicOperations.FixedTimeEquals(
                                    providedSignatureBytes,
                                    expectedSignatureBytes
                                )
                            )
                        then
                            false
                        else
                            let payload = System.Text.Encoding.UTF8.GetString(payloadBytes)
                            let payloadParts = payload.Split(':')

                            if payloadParts.Length <> 2 then
                                false
                            else
                                match System.Int64.TryParse(payloadParts[0]) with
                                | true, expiresAt ->
                                    let now = System.DateTimeOffset.UtcNow.ToUnixTimeSeconds()
                                    now <= expiresAt
                                | false, _ -> false
                    with
                    | _ -> false
```

